TopicTitle: The Game Keeps Crashing after trying to install mods and then uninstall them

Articles.Content:
I am using KSP Version 1.3.1 and the game keeps crashing after I tried installing USITools, KW Rocketry, WarpPlugin (Interstellar), DistantObjectEnhancement, and TacLifeSupport. I installed them, they didn't work and then I uninstalled them. Then, the game keeps crashing after it gets to "MODULEMANAGER: FINAL" when loading.

Log:

Spoiler

https://www.dropbox.com/s/g1bp5jgjure0293/output_log.txt?dl=0 (FYI: I can't paste the entire log here because the forum keeps crashing each time I do that)

 

 

Oops! I forgot to mention that I also tried installing FASA with them.

Edited January 4, 2018 by KingWilliamB
Fixed Log

Quote 

ModuleManager.2.6.25.dll
ModuleManager.2.7.5.dll
ModuleManager.2.8.1.dll
ModuleManager.3.0.0.dll
ModuleManager.3.0.1.dll
 

You have five different versions of Module manager. While this in and of itself is not a problem because only the latest version will load, it shows that some of the mods you tried to install are outdated. 

I recommend going through all the mods you have installed and make sure they are all compatible with KSP 1.3.1.
Thanks so much! That fixed it!
